snippet.title: Pascal Poupart
snippet.description: This channel includes video lectures by Pascal Poupart, who is a professor in the David R. Cheriton School of Computer Science at the University of Waterloo (https://cs.uwaterloo.ca/~ppoupart/).  He is a member of the Waterloo AI Institute and the Vector Institute.  His research focuses on the development of algorithms for machine learning, reinforcement learning and reasoning under uncertainty with application to natural language processing and assistive technologies.
